            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch fixes a bug in the NFS server where it silently drops directory attribute changes requested by clients if they cannot be encoded. The patch recalls delegations when such failures occur, as required by RFC 8881. It distinguishes between genuine encoding failures and benign cases where no attributes are requested. The patch also removes an unnecessary check and fixes NULL pointer handling issues.",
